    "discriminators": [
     "An impulsive footfall train, but the four-legged gait and claw-patter give a faster, less evenly-spaced onset train than a human's ~2 /s biped rhythm. A tendency only: a dog's paws and a person in socks are the same physics.",
     "Species is semantic — nothing in the spectrum says 'elephant' rather than 'large dog'. The signal only confirms 'footsteps'.",
     "UCS routes hooves to FOOTSTEPS-HORSE and herds or stampedes to MOVEMENT-ANIMALS; a very dense, non-resolvable onset train should go there."
    ],
