    "discriminators": [
     "A biped gait: an impulsive onset train at roughly 1.5–2.5 steps/s walking (up to ~3.5 running) with genuinely high onset_periodicity. That rate-plus-regularity pair is the core measurable claim.",
     "Unvoiced and impulsive, so it never competes with VOICES or CROWDS despite the shared human context.",
     "UCS puts EVERY surface and shoe here, so the material axis (bright slappy concrete vs damped grass vs crunchy high-frequency snow) varies wildly WITHIN the class — which is why spectral_centroid carries a wide deviation and a low weight here. Surface separates recordings, not subcategories.",
     "Slower and duller than FOOTSTEPS-HORSE; a human running (~3 /s) is where it blurs into FOOTSTEPS-ANIMAL."
